{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id5a20c0a7-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c","identifier":"/us/usc/t29/s165"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"165"},"text":"§ 165.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Conflict of laws","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Wherever the application of the provisions of section 272 of chapter 10 of the Act entitled “An Act to establish a uniform system of bankruptcy throughout the United States”, approved ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1898-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1898","children":[],"tail":", and Acts amendatory thereof and supplementary thereto (U.S.C., title 11, sec. 672), conflicts with the application of the provisions of this subchapter, this subchapter shall prevail: "},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"Provided","children":[],"tail":", That in any situation where the provisions of this subchapter cannot be validly enforced, the provisions of such other Acts shall remain in full force and effect."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id5a20c0a8-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1935-07-05/ch372/s15"},"text":"July 5, 1935, ch. 372, § 15","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/49/457"},"text":"49 Stat. 457","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1947-06-23/ch120"},"text":"June 23, 1947, ch. 120","children":[],"tail":", title I, § 101, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/61/151"},"text":"61 Stat. 151","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id5a20c0a9-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id5a20c0aa-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id5a20c0ab-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Act approved ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1898-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1898","children":[],"tail":", referred to in text, popularly known as the Bankruptcy Act, was classified generally to former Title 11, Bankruptcy, and was repealed effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1979-10-01"},"text":"Oct. 1, 1979","children":[],"tail":", by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/598"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–598","children":[],"tail":", §§ 401(a), 402(a), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-11-06"},"text":"Nov. 6, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/2682"},"text":"92 Stat. 2682","children":[],"tail":", section 101 of which enacted revised Title 11."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id5a20c0ac-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1947—Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1947-06-23"},"text":"June 23, 1947","children":[],"tail":", amended section generally by inserting new subject matter which was formerly covered by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t29/s164"},"text":"section 164 of this title","children":[],"tail":". Section formerly referred to separability provisions, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t29/s166"},"text":"section 166 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id5a20c0ad-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id5a20c0ae-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1947 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For effective date of amendment by act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1947-06-23"},"text":"June 23, 1947","children":[],"tail":", see section 104 of act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1947-06-23"},"text":"June 23, 1947","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t29/s151"},"text":"section 151 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
